From Rob Unverzagt Subject Re space food sticks In article writes I had spacefood sticks just about every morning for breakfast in first and second grade They came in Chocolate strawberry and peanut butter and were cylinders about long and in diameter wrapped in yellow space foil well it seemed like space foil at the time Wasn't there a plain flavor too They looked more like some kind of extruded industrial product than food perfectly smooth cylinders with perfectly smooth Kinda The taste is hard to describe although I remember it It was most certainly more candy than say a modern Power Sort of a toffee injected with The chocolate Power Bar is a rough approximation of the Strawberry An other post described it as like a microwaved Tootsie Roll which captures the texture pretty As for taste they were like candy only not very sweet does that make sense I recall liking them for their texture not I guess I have well developed texture Man these were my ' It was obligatory to eat a few while watching Captain Scarlet Does anybody else remember that as long as we're off the topic of space Shag Rob Unverzagt Tuesday is soylent green